messageBody:
1. Install ant from http://jakarta.apache.org/ant
2. Download the optional.jar from http://jakarta.apache.org/ant, and place it in the ant/lib dir
3. copy the junit jars to ant/lib.
4. read the any manual.
5. search the JUnit group archive on "Ant".

have fun,

- Yishay
